  • public class AsyncCallSucceedEvent
extends GwtEvent<AsyncCallSucceedHandler>
    Event fired after any asynchronous call to the server performed by GWTP MVP has succeeded. Such asynchronous calls only occur when using code splitting.
    Author:
    Philippe Beaudoin
    See Also:
    AsyncCallSucceedHandler, AsyncCallStartEvent, AsyncCallFailEvent
